This paper deals with machine translation, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of neural networks and embeddings also suggests a connection to deep learning and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper involves statistical modeling, which is a common theme in machine learning (ML) and computational linguistics (CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
